That is interesting. Wasn't expecting to be able to store not declared enum combinations inside the enum variable.
So.. same as happens with the `NetPermissionFlags`,  could remove every static_cast and do something like:
```c++
PriorityLevel levels{0};
for (const auto& level: SplitString(str, ',')) {
   levels = levels | benchmark::StringToPriority(level);
}
return levels;
```

Which.. can make the software crash if I pass a combination of tags that isn't declared (e.g. "medium, low") and call `PriorityToString(levels)` (at the assertion point).

